WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#71: FILE: arch/ia64/pci/pci.c:320:
 static void __devinit

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*bus_res)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct pci_bus_resource)...)
#218: FILE: drivers/pci/bus.c:25:
+	bus_res = kzalloc(sizeof(struct pci_bus_resource), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

WARNING:OOM_MESSAGE: Possible unnecessary 'out of memory' message
#220: FILE: drivers/pci/bus.c:27:
+	if (!bus_res) {
+		dev_err(&bus->dev, "can't add %pR resource\n", res);

WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#275: FILE: drivers/pci/probe.c:395:
 void __devinit pci_read_bridge_bases(struct pci_bus *child)

CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '+' (ctx:VxV)
#288: FILE: drivers/pci/probe.c:410:
+		child->resource[i] = &dev->resource[PCI_BRIDGE_RESOURCES+i];
 		                                                        ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

